00:00:52.690 --> 00:00:56.780
We know what you do on the show,
but talk about the genesis,

00:00:56.780 --> 00:00:59.000
where this idea came from.

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:02.610
SETH MACFARLANE: I've always
been a huge fan of sci-fi

00:01:02.610 --> 00:01:04.290
in many different forms.

00:01:04.290 --> 00:01:08.300
And it had been a while
since I had seen something

00:01:08.300 --> 00:01:12.560
on television that was episodic
from start to finish, like

00:01:12.560 --> 00:01:16.520
"The Twilight Zone," like "Star
Trek," where I was being told

00:01:16.520 --> 00:01:23.160
a story, a brand new story
that had a beginning, middle,

00:01:23.160 --> 00:01:25.430
and end all on its
own on a weekly basis.

00:01:25.430 --> 00:01:26.120
And I miss that.

00:01:26.120 --> 00:01:28.239
And I kind of wanted
it back, because that's

00:01:28.239 --> 00:01:29.280
what I remember watching.

00:01:29.280 --> 00:01:33.200
And there's a lot of great
serialized sci-fi out there,

00:01:33.200 --> 00:01:35.720
but there's really
nothing that presents you

00:01:35.720 --> 00:01:39.719
with the new idea of the
week, and that was what

00:01:39.719 --> 00:01:41.010
we're out to do with this show.

00:01:41.010 --> 00:01:43.730
And at the same time,
obviously, I come out of comedy.

00:01:43.730 --> 00:01:46.700
And you know, the other
thing I had not seen

00:01:46.700 --> 00:01:52.790
was a sort of aggressive
casualization of life onboard

00:01:52.790 --> 00:01:56.630
a spaceship, where people
kind of talk over each other

00:01:56.630 --> 00:02:03.600
and behave in a not so formal
way, as I would imagine

00:02:03.600 --> 00:02:07.250
is what day to day life is
like in the actual military.

00:02:07.250 --> 00:02:12.680
So it's where there's moments
of realism, where it's just

00:02:12.680 --> 00:02:14.734
people behaving like
people, where they're not

00:02:14.734 --> 00:02:15.650
always so buttoned up.

00:02:15.650 --> 00:02:18.770
So you know, those are sort
of the ingredients that

00:02:18.770 --> 00:02:20.270
were, I think,
foremost in my mind

00:02:20.270 --> 00:02:22.190
when I was coming
up with this idea.

00:02:22.190 --> 00:02:22.940
KEVIN BELK: Great.

00:02:22.940 --> 00:02:24.773
And Liz, we'll start
with you and go around.

00:02:24.773 --> 00:02:27.620
But just what are your roles
in the film, on the TV series,

00:02:27.620 --> 00:02:28.340
sorry.

