- The coolest thing
to me that we're doing

00:03:21.940 --> 00:03:23.380
is we are doing model work.

00:03:23.380 --> 00:03:24.940
- Seth really wanted
a subconscious

00:03:24.940 --> 00:03:28.180
feel of a real model, as opposed
to a computer generated one.

00:03:28.180 --> 00:03:30.780
We put the best of
both worlds together,

00:03:30.780 --> 00:03:33.670
designed it on the computer,
being able to print it out

00:03:33.670 --> 00:03:35.890
from within, and then
we have this action

00:03:35.890 --> 00:03:37.660
object that we could shoot.

00:03:37.660 --> 00:03:38.620
- It's not bad, right?

00:03:38.620 --> 00:03:40.090
- No, it's good.

00:03:40.090 --> 00:03:41.980
You paint some
flames on the side,

00:03:41.980 --> 00:03:43.720
maybe like a rainbow unicorn.

00:03:43.720 --> 00:03:44.470
You got something.

00:03:44.470 --> 00:03:48.300
- The more complex shots
of the Orville are CGI.

00:03:48.300 --> 00:03:51.590
But when you see the Orville
fly by, or if its a close shot,

00:03:51.590 --> 00:03:54.460
or if it doesn't have to do
something really acrobatic,

00:03:54.460 --> 00:03:55.180
those are models.

00:03:55.180 --> 00:03:57.540
We built an actual
model of the Orville.

00:03:57.540 --> 00:04:02.080
There's something that still
feels artificial and cartoonish

00:04:02.080 --> 00:04:03.460
about a CGI spaceship.

00:04:03.460 --> 00:04:06.940
Even now there's nothing
that really smells

00:04:06.940 --> 00:04:10.600
like a model that's real and has
been designed by human hands.

00:04:10.600 --> 00:04:13.720
As a sci-fi nerd,
that's probably--

00:04:13.720 --> 00:04:16.080
might be the biggest
thrill for me.

00:04:16.080 --> 00:04:18.040
[END PLAYBACK]

