But it's, like, I've
seen a lot of shows

00:31:59.560 --> 00:32:02.110
that have tried to do
the sci-fi comedy thing

00:32:02.110 --> 00:32:03.490
and crash and burn.

00:32:03.490 --> 00:32:06.596
And it's a thing
that-- in movies, I

00:32:06.596 --> 00:32:07.720
think it's a little easier.

00:32:07.720 --> 00:32:09.010
Because it's a one off.

00:32:09.010 --> 00:32:10.510
It's big and splashy,
and you're not

00:32:10.510 --> 00:32:15.070
being asked to invest in people
who aren't always surrounded

00:32:15.070 --> 00:32:16.330
by amazing special effects.

00:32:16.330 --> 00:32:18.760
Sometimes you're just
standing in a room talking.

00:32:18.760 --> 00:32:19.850
And It's got to feel real.

00:32:19.850 --> 00:32:24.110
And if it's too funny,
the stakes go away.

00:32:24.110 --> 00:32:27.500
And if it's too serious, then
the show becomes too dark.

00:32:27.500 --> 00:32:28.510
So for me, it's tone.

00:32:28.510 --> 00:32:32.500
And I feel like,
interestingly, like we've

00:32:32.500 --> 00:32:36.550
leaned, in recent episodes,
a little more into the drama

00:32:36.550 --> 00:32:39.820
than I thought we would,
but it's kind of working.

00:32:39.820 --> 00:32:45.080
And I follow a lot of feedback
online, as much as I can.

00:32:45.080 --> 00:32:47.920
I love hearing what people
are saying about the show,

00:32:47.920 --> 00:32:49.810
and I really do
take it to heart.

00:32:49.810 --> 00:32:57.340
And that seems to be the overall
sentiment is, like, look,

00:32:57.340 --> 00:32:58.759
we're buying these stories.

00:32:58.759 --> 00:32:59.800
We're into these stories.

00:32:59.800 --> 00:33:01.310
We're buying the
sci-fi of it all.

00:33:01.310 --> 00:33:05.140
You don't have to throw a pie
in somebody's face once a page.

00:33:05.140 --> 00:33:06.790
We'll stay with
you, which is great.

00:33:06.790 --> 00:33:10.030
Because that's what's
fresh about it for me, too.

00:33:10.030 --> 00:33:12.880
And so tone is
really the big thing

00:33:12.880 --> 00:33:15.190
that I've learned a
lot about this season.

00:33:15.190 --> 00:33:15.940
KEVIN BELK: Great.

00:33:15.940 --> 00:33:17.773
Well, thank you guys
so much for being here.

00:33:17.773 --> 00:33:20.440
"Orville" is on Fox,
Thursday at 9-10 Central.

00:33:20.440 --> 00:33:21.970
So thanks so much, guys.

00:33:21.970 --> 00:33:24.720
